item.title: 'There's no quarantine': Crew on virus-hit cruise ship say their work puts them at great risk
Dalai Lama cancels all public engagements as coronavirus death toll passes 1,100
China struggles to return to work after the coronavirus lockdown
item.description: Beijing's normally bustling shopping district is desolate, after an extended public holiday ended for much of China. Most of the stores in the popular Wangfujing shopping malls are closed, and one popular restaurant has no customers and has resorted to selling its produce in order to make ends meet.

item.title: Trump's Roger Stone power play reveals a presidency unleashed
For the first time in 9 years, two nations are going toe-to-toe in Syria
item.description: Syria's curse, as its conflict rumbles slowly towards its first decade, has always been how new forces enter the war just when it seems that exhaustion might slow everyone down.

item.title: High-level murder investigation grips tiny mountain kingdom
item.description: Maesaiah Thabane, the first lady of the tiny mountain kingdom of Lesotho, always knew how to make an entrance.

item.title: Sanders finally got his televised celebration, but Buttigieg made him sweat
Watch the speeches: Sanders declares victory and others say their goodbyes
item.description: Sen. Bernie Sanders said his victory in New Hampshire was the beginning of the end for President Donald Trump, as fellow Democratic candidates Andrew Yang and Michael Bennet dropped out of the race.

item.title: Trump's historical place defined by his amorality
item.description: Scandals, large or small, mark most American presidencies. What makes Donald Trump historically unique is something different.

item.title: Firefighter ordered suspended without pay after trying to rescue an elderly woman from a fire
item.description: Before anyone can become a firefighter, they first must take an oath: a promise to put the lives of others before their own, even if it means making the ultimate sacrifice.

item.title: Kobe Bryant and his daughter laid to rest
item.description: NBA legend Kobe Bryant and his 13-year-old daughter, Gianna, were buried Friday at a Southern California cemetery following their deaths January 26 in a helicopter crash, death certificates released Tuesday by Los Angeles County officials show.

item.title: Woman jailed for trying to open plane door mid-flight
item.description: A British woman who tried to open the door of a plane mid-flight was sentenced to two years in jail Wednesday.

item.title: Record temperatures hit Antarctica as tourism rises
item.description: A research base at the tip of Antarctica recorded the highest temperature on record for the continent. With an influx of tourists, CNN's Robyn Curnow look at what climate activists are saying is the long-term forecast for this remote land.

item.title: Pope rejects a proposal to allow married priests in the Amazon
item.description: Last year, Pope Francis called for "bold proposals" to meet the spiritual needs of Catholics in the Amazon, a vast region with a scarcity of clerics.

item.title: National security adviser says Vindman brothers weren't fired -- Trump says military should decide their fate
item.description: National security adviser Robert O'Brien says there was "absolutely" no retaliation against Lt. Col. Alexander Vindman and his twin brother, who were removed from their White House jobs last week in fallout from President Donald Trump's impeachment acquittal.

item.title: Why travel bans from China might not be effective
item.description: How effective are travel bans in stopping the spread of coronavirus? CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta joins Anderson Cooper to answer viewers' questions about the coronavirus outbreak. Watch "Full Circle" every weeknight at 5 p.m. ET.

item.title: Big wave surfer 'stable' after suffering sickening wipeout
item.description: Big wave surfer Alex Botelho is "stable and conscious" in hospital after suffering a sickening wipeout during a competition at Nazare, Portugal Tuesday.

item.title: Ex-prison official shoots himself dead in court after being sentenced to 3 years in jail
item.description: A former Russian prison service official died by suicide in a Moscow court on Wednesday after he was sentenced to three years in jail, Russian state news agency TASS reported.

item.title: Two Ohio State football players were arrested on felony rape and kidnapping charges
item.description: Two Ohio State football players were arrested early Wednesday on felony rape and kidnapping charges, jail records show.

item.title: Parents, grandparents to blame for half of child poisonings, study says
item.description: Over half of poisonings in children under five are due to parents, grandparents taking dangerous pills out of packaging, study says

item.title: Newborn giant planet discovered 330 light-years away
item.description: Researchers just located a baby giant planet orbiting a young star just 330 light-years from Earth, making it the closest of its kind to us.

item.title: Ancient turtle had a horned shell that was nearly ten feet long
item.description: About five to ten million years ago, giant turtles that dwarfed humans reigned supreme in South America. Its shell reached nearly 10 feet in length and weighed 2,500 pounds.

item.title: Photo of squabbling mice wins award
item.description: The sight of two mice scurrying across a London Underground platform in the evening is, to many, an unwelcome feature of life in the city.

item.title: Facebook suspends dating service rollout in Europe after Dublin HQ searched
item.description: Facebook has suspended the rollout of its dating service in Europe planned for the eve of Valentine's Day after officials from the Irish data regulator searched its offices.

item.title: Heavyweight boxer Wilder takes swipe at rival Joshua
item.description: Deontay Wilder has taken a verbal swipe at heavyweight rival Anthony Joshua while preparing for his rematch with Tyson Fury in Las Vegas next week.

item.title: Toobin: This didn't even happen during Nixon era
item.description: CNN legal analyst Jeffrey Toobin reacts to President Donald Trump "injecting himself" into the federal case against the President's longtime confidant Roger Stone.

item.title: He was six inches from being hit with a steel beam. A steering wheel saved him
item.description: A Michigan man calls himself blessed after a steel beam came inches from hitting his chest.

item.title: Trump tweets clip of comedian in MAGA hat, but misses the punchline
item.description: CNN's Brooke Baldwin speaks to writer Matt Wilstein about President Donald Trump apparently misinterpreting a "Curb Your Enthusiasm" clip where Larry David mockingly wears a MAGA hat to repel people around him.

item.title: A father said his toddler was abducted from their driveway. Police now say he fabricated some details
item.description: Florida authorities were on the hunt for 3-year-old Madeline Mejia on Monday after her father told them she was abducted from their driveway by strangers. Now, police say, some of the details of his story weren't true and the young girl was actually with her biological mother.

item.title: La Liga defends apparent racist gesture by Real Mallorca coach
item.description: The actions of a Real Mallorca coach who appeared to make a racist gesture during Sunday's match against Espanyol have been defended by La Liga, Spanish football's top division.

item.title: Homeowners lose legal challenge over Tate Modern visitors looking into their apartments
item.description: Residents of a high-rise apartment block in London have lost a long-running legal bid to stop visitors to the Tate Modern art museum from looking through their windows -- after a judge ruled that they could solve the problem simply by closing their blinds.

item.title: Google just released 1,000 new images of gorgeous landscapes
item.description: Google has shared bird's-eye-view images of some of Earth's most stunning landscapes from space for years now, and it just released its largest update to its Google Earth View collection with 1,000 new images.

item.title: This couple made history in Northern Ireland
item.description: A Belfast couple made history after British MPs voted to extend same-sex marriage to Northern Ireland last July.

item.title: This is what Samsung's $1,380 flip phone looks like
item.description: A year after the botched rollout of its first foldable smartphone, Samsung unveiled the Samsung Galaxy Z Flip. It features a foldable design and split-screen capabilities.

item.title: The world's oldest living man is 112. His secret is to just keep smiling and never get angry
item.description: Chitetsu Watanabe turns 113 next month, but he got an early birthday present from Guinness World Records, which confirmed that he is the world's oldest living man.

item.title: 'Firefall' is set to return to Yosemite National Park
item.description: It's that time of year again when Mother Nature plays a magic trick at Yosemite National Park and makes it look like lava is flowing off a cliff.

item.title: Museum pleads for return of stolen bonsai trees worth thousands
item.description: Two bonsai trees worth thousands of dollars that require special care were stolen from a Washington state museum, the museum said.

item.title: Viral video breaks down US voting system
item.description: Dayton, Ohio, rapper YelloPain's video for "My Vote Don't Count" explains why every election is important. HLN's Melissa Knowles reports why the video is gaining traction online.

item.title: Food tastes better when you eat at a table with a tablecloth, study finds
item.description: If you're hoping to impress a date with a romantic home-cooked meal this Valentine's Day, don't forget the tablecloth.

item.title: Tiger Woods mulling details of proposed lucrative global golf tour
item.description: He says it is a "natural evolution" but Tiger Woods is wary of jumping ship to a proposed new world golf tour.

item.title: Playing golf may help older adults live longer, study says
item.description: President Trump has spent more than 260 days at one of his golf clubs during his first three years in office as of February 2, according to CNN's tally.

item.title: A solar-powered 'Meerkat' is protecting South Africa's rhinos
item.description: In South Africa's biggest national park, a camouflaged system of radars, cameras and sensors stands guard.

item.title: The hated British train that just won't die
item.description: Every day, Pacer trains trundle through some of the most beautiful scenery in northern England, across rolling dales and moody moorlands, before pulling up in the great cities of the region: Manchester, Leeds and Sheffield.

item.title: Worker on board the Diamond Princess cruise liner says the crew are at greater risk of coronavirus
Dalai Lama cancels public engagements due to coronavirus
Unexpected four-week break in middle of F1 calendar
item.description: The 2020 Chinese Grand Prix has been postponed due to the deadly coronavirus outbreak, Formula One announced on Wednesday.

item.title: Beijing to enact new measures as 160 million head back to work
item.description: China expects around 160 million employees to return to their workplaces in the next week, as the country seeks to minimize the economic impact of the novel coronavirus.

item.title: Hong Kong investigating if virus spread via one high-rise's pipes
item.description: Early Tuesday morning, health officials in Hong Kong partially evacuated residents from an apartment block over fears the coronavirus may have been transmitted via the building's pipes.

item.title: Hear what cruise ship employees have to say about on board conditions
item.description: Nearly 1,000 crew members on board the Diamond Princess cruise ship are not under quarantine despite the novel coronavirus outbreak. Without quarantine protection, many fear contracting the virus. CNN's Matt Rivers reports from Japan.

item.title: Trump thanks DOJ for intervening in ally's case
item.description: • Analysis: Susan Collins' defense of Trump vote keeps looking worse and worse
